   "source": [
    "## Work Stability"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To better capture the borrower’s employment stability, we created a new feature **work_stability**, which measures the proportion of a borrower’s lifetime spent in working.\n",
    "\n",
    "This feature was computed as follows, and its values ranged between 0 and 1:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\text{Work Stability} = \\frac{\\text{Employment Experience}}{(\\text{Age} - 16)}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "- A higher value indicated that the borrower had been employed for most of their life, suggesting greater financial stability and a lower probability of default.\n",
    "- A lower value indicated limited employment experience relative to age, implying lower financial stability and a higher probability of default."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 24,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df['work_stability'] = df['person_emp_exp'] / (df['person_age'] - 16)"
   ]
  },
